# Cursor Rules — Automated Social Media Agency MVP

## Code Style
- Always write concise, technical Python.
- Prefer functional and declarative programming patterns over imperative code.
- Use type hints on all function signatures.
- Keep functions small and single-purpose.

## Error Handling
- Implement strict error handling for ALL network requests (try/except with
  specific exception types, timeout parameters, retry logic where appropriate).
- Never silently swallow exceptions; always log or re-raise.

## Dependencies & Tooling
- Use the `uv` package manager for all dependency operations.
- Pin dependency versions in pyproject.toml.

## Project Tracking (CRITICAL)
- At the END of every task or phase, you MUST autonomously update
  `project_overview.txt` so the human operator knows exactly what has been
  completed and what the next steps are. No exceptions.
